==English==
===Noun===
'''Coorg''' (Plural: Coorgs)

# A mountainous region found in south western India. Also known locally as [[w:Kodagu]].
  Formerly a kingdom and then a state till 1956. Coorg is now a district of Karnataka State in the Republic of India.

# A person of ethnic race originating from Coorg (kodagu) in India. Also known locally as Kodava (Plural: Kodavas).